title: New Zealand Woman Dies Dam Flooding at Aratiatia Rapids
text:
An Auckland University student died swimming in the Aratiatia Rapids, a section of the Waikato River in New Zealand on Monday after being swept away by the current when a nearby dam's floodgates opened.
Twenty-one-year-old Rachael De Jong was swimming in the famous rapids with four other friends. According to the Waikato Times , the swimmers were standing on a rocky outcrop in the middle of the river when the dam opened, releasing a 22,000 gallons-per-second current.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below The Daily Mail reports that, while other tourists watched (and filmed) from a nearby viewing platform, one member of the group, who had successfully swum to the river's bank, tried to pull his friends across. Two safely reached the shore, but De Jong was swept away along with two other of her friends. While they both survived the incident, rescuers recovered her body later that day.
